{{Infobox film | name = Am Sklavenmarkt | image = {{CSS image crop |Image = Johann Schwarzer movies about 1906.jpg |bSize = 300 |cWidth = 300 |cHeight = 200 |Alt = People in front of a tent. }} | image_size = | caption = Scene from the film | director = [[Johann Schwarzer]] | producer = [[:de:Saturn-Film|Saturn-Film]] | writer = | narrator = | starring = | music = | cinematography = | editing = | distributor = | released = 1906/1907 | runtime = | country = [[Austria]] | language = [[Silent film]] | budget = | preceded_by = | followed_by = }}
'''''Am Sklavenmarkt''' (German: "at the [[slavery|slave market]]")'' is a [[Short film|short]] [[1907 in film|1907]] [[Austria]]n [[pornographic film]] [[Film director|directed]] by [[Johann Schwarzer]] (1880-1914) at his studio [[:de:Saturn-Film|Saturn-Film]] company. The film is {{convert|50|m|ft}} long. It is possibly the first [[Cinema of Austria|Austrian film]] ever made and one of the earliest films to use [[eroticism|erotic]] elements in Austrian films.{{Citation needed|date=April 2010}}
The first image is taken from ''Am Sklavenmarkt''.<ref>''Im Kino erlebe ich die Welt - 100 Jahre Kino und Film in Österreich'' (1996) by Walter Fritz Vienna, p.146, {{ISBN|978-3-85447-661-0}}</ref>
==Story== A [[pasha]] sits on a mat on the grass in front of a round tent, smoking from his water-pipe, ready to buy some new slave girls. His servant calls the seller and his two [[henchmen]], who bring forth four girls in patterned [[burnoose]]s. The first is totally undressed and sent into the tent; the next girl gets [[Toplessness|topless]] and is also sent into the tent; the third is forced to undress by the henchmen and also sent inside. The fourth, apparently a younger girl, is dismissed by the [[Arab]] after showing her small, firm breasts, and she goes back with the henchmen. After a customary argument over the price, the slave master goes away happy.
